A '''cold-energy battery''' utilizes the properties of an advanced [[phase-change material]] (PCM) to maintain temperature as [[battery thermal management]]. As with a standard [[Battery (electricity)|electrical battery]], a cold energy battery stores energy and releases depending on the energy demand on it. It can then be recharged by placing in a temperature environment conducive to the phase change properties of the PCM.

